According to a report by Intel Market Research, the India High-End Copper Foil Market was valued at USD 89 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 96 million in 2025 to USD 145 million by 2032, registering a CAGR of 8.5% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust expansion as India accelerates investments in electric vehicles (EVs), advanced electronics manufacturing, lithium-ion batteries, and next-generation telecommunications infrastructure. Government initiatives such as the Production Linked Incentive (PLI) scheme and the Faster Adoption and Manufacturing of Electric Vehicles (FAME) program are further strengthening domestic manufacturing capabilities and boosting demand for premium-grade copper foil used in high-performance applications.
